Task #8: Enhanced Two-Factor Authentication with Login Enforcement & Multiple Methods

Changes:
- Modified POST /api/auth/login to enforce 2FA: when user has any 2FA method 
  enabled, returns {requires2FA, methods, tempToken} instead of completing login.
  Uses fail-closed error handling (returns 500 on error, never bypasses 2FA).
- Added POST /api/auth/verify-2fa endpoint: validates temp token + chosen method 
  (TOTP/email OTP/recovery passphrase) then completes login with sanitized user.
- Added POST /api/auth/resend-2fa-email for re-sending email OTP during login.
- Email OTP enablement uses setup+verify flow:
  POST /api/2fa/email-otp/setup sends 6-digit code to user's email,
  POST /api/2fa/email-otp/verify validates the code and enables emailOtpEnabled.
  POST /api/2fa/email-otp/disable to turn off.
- TOTP uses setup+verify flow: /api/totp/setup (QR+secret), /api/totp/verify-setup
  (validates 6-digit code from authenticator app), /api/totp/disable.
- Recovery passphrase uses setup with confirmation: /api/2fa/passphrase/setup
  (bcrypt hashed, requires passphrase in body), /api/2fa/passphrase/disable.
- Enhanced GET /api/totp/status to return all method statuses (totp, emailOtp, passphrase).
- In-memory pending2FA map with 10-min TTL and 60s auto-cleanup interval.
- Added "2fa_email" to OTP model type enum to prevent validation errors.

Model changes (server/models.ts):
- Added emailOtpEnabled (Boolean), recoveryPassphrase (String, select:false), 
  recoveryPassphraseEnabled (Boolean) to UserSchema.

Frontend changes:
- Login.tsx: Added 2FA verification step with method tabs (TOTP/email/passphrase),
  error handling, resend email OTP button, and back-to-login button.
  After 2FA verification, email-verification gate re-applied for unverified clients.
- TwoFactorSetup.tsx: Complete redesign with 3 method cards. TOTP (QR+verify code),
  Email OTP (send code to email + verify code to enable), Passphrase (set+confirm).
- use-auth.ts: useLogin hook now handles requires2FA response without navigation.

Security fixes:
- Login route uses fail-closed catch (returns 500, not auto-login on error).
- verify-2fa reloads user without +totpSecret/+recoveryPassphrase before responding.
- OTP model enum updated to include "2fa_email" type.
